This template is used to generate the above/title section in a politics sidebar
== Usage ==
<pre>
{{sidebar with collapsible lists
| name = {{subst:PAGENAME}}
| wraplinks = true
| bodyclass = vcard
| liststyle = text-align: left

| title = {{politics sidebar title
  | country = <!-- country -->
  | title = <!-- country or the country -->
  | image = Coat of arms of the Netherlands.svg
  | alt =
  }}

| list1title =
| list1 =

| below = {{politics sidebar below|<!-- country or the country -->}}
}}
</pre>

== Parameters ==
; country : the name of the country, it should correspond to the title of the article about the country 
:: Example: {{para|country|Netherlands}}
; title : the name of the country or region corresponding to the article named "Siyaasadda title"
:: Example: {{para|title|the Netherlands}}
; image : the file name of a representative image
:: Example: {{para|image|Coat of arms of the Netherlands.svg}}
; size : the width of the image (default is frameless)
:: Example: {{para|size|150px}}
; alt : alternative text for the image
:: Example: {{para|alt|The coat of arms for the Netherlands depicting ...}}
; border: add a border around the image
:: Example: {{para|border|y}}

== Regions that are not countries ==
; region: the name of the region, it should correspond to the title of the article about the region
:: Example: {{para|region|North Dakota}}

== Modifying the linking ==
; link : by default, the title parameter is used for both the link text and the link.  to use a different value for the link, set link to a value which corresponds to the article named "Politics of link"

== Removing the separator ==
; separator-width: by default, the horizontal rule at the bottom of the box has width 1px, to remove the separator, set {{para|separator-width|0}}.

